Exercise 2: Classification with Naive Bayes classifier
=====================================================

Load a dataset with subject s01 and the VT mask. Slice it using your sample
attributes slicer so that there are only two categories: monkeys and
ladybugs. Then split the samples again into training and testing data. Use
these two plits of the data as input into the Naive Bayes classifier given
below.


